On International Holocaust Remembrance Day, the article highlights the importance of remembering and mourning the millions of Jews and other groups who were targeted and killed during the Holocaust. It also condemns the recent rise in antisemitism, particularly in the aftermath of a Hamas attack on Israel. The author emphasizes the need to stand up against hate and antisemitism and to ensure that history is not denied or distorted. The article mentions the National Strategy to Combat Antisemitism and the personal experiences of the author in educating their family about the Holocaust. The message concludes by expressing solidarity with the Jewish community and a commitment to fighting hate and bringing the hostages home.